&quot;Eugenius Harvey Outerbridge (1860 – November 11, 1932) was a businessman and promoter of patent fiberboard, and the first chairman of the interstate agency known then as the Port of New York Authority. The Port Authority bridge, the Outerbridge Crossing, was named for him.&quot;
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eugenius_Harvey_Outerbridge" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eugenius_Harvey_Outerbridge</a>

In 1916 he was President of the Chamber of Commerce, see article with drawing in <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030272/1916-06-18/ed-1/seq-46/" rel="nofollow">The sun., June 18, 1916, SIXTH SECTION PREPAREDNESS NUMBER, Page 6</a> &quot;VITAL INTEREST OF BUSINESS WORLD IN NATIONAL DEFENCE&quot; by Eugenius H. Outerbridge
